         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Legal Services</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>CU240</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="79100000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Cardiff University (the “University”) intends to run a procurement to establish a Legal Services Framework (the “Framework”), which is likely to be split into lots. It is envisioned that the framework will be used to appoint law firms to act for, and provide advice to, the University in relation to a wide range of its legal needs.</P>
               <P>It is estimated that the framework will run for an initial 2 years with the option to extend in 1 year periods, at the University's discretion, for a further 2 periods (4 years maximum).</P>
               <P>The framework will likely cover a wide range of legal disciplines including, but not limited to, the following areas of law: Property; Projects; Employment; Commercial; Corporate; IP; and Higher Education.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Legal Services Framework — Lot 1</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>1</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="79100000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKL22"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>This notice is not a call for competition. This notice is to act as an early market engagement exercise to enable the University to engage with suppliers to better understand the market and explore potential ways of structuring how it engages it external legal services.</P>
                  <P>The University intends to host a supplier engagement day, subject to sufficient interest from the market. The supplier engagement day, if held, will be hosted to all interested economic operators on 3.5.2018. Further details of the event are provided at Section VI.3 (Additional information) below. It is important that, should you be interested in such event, you respond to this notice expressing your interest no later than one week after publication.</P>
                  <P>This market engagement exercise is intended to inform and assist the University in designing the Framework. It is estimated that the framework procurement would commence summer 2018.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>Please note that the University is currently undecided as to how this Framework will be lotted (i.e. how many lots, the scope of each lot etc).</P>
                  <P>It is envisioned that any market engagement will assist the University in determining how to best split this Framework into lots (if at all). Any further details regarding lots would be further communicated within any subsequent contract notice (if any).</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="2">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Legal Services Framework — Lot 2</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>2</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="79100000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKL22"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>As per II.2.4 of 'Legal Services Framework — Lot 1' above.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>As per II.2.14 of 'Legal Services Framework — Lot 1' above.</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-07-02</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>The purpose of the supplier engagement event is to provide:</P>
               <P>— the market with an understanding of what the University’s requirements and intentions are regarding its legal services,</P>
               <P>— the University with an understanding of how to structure its requirement to enable best working and maximise the market interest in the Framework, and</P>
               <P>— the University with the market’s opinion on what it deems to be some key areas of legal need facing the University over the next 4 years; for example, the potential legal implications arising from students being recognised as “consumers”.</P>
               <P>The supplier engagement event will be dependent on the amrket's level of interest in engaging with The University at this stage, and will either comprise individual meetings with interested parties or, alternatively, a 2-hour event at The University. This event will include a presentation from The University and the opportunity for collaborative working and questions. All economic operators should note their interest in attending the supplier engagement event through the “noted interest” option on the Sell2Wales website.</P>
               <P>The University envision a note/recording of the day being taken and being made available for those who were unable to attend.</P>
               <P>This notice if for information only and the University reserves the right not to commence any competitive procurement following this notice or the market engagement event. The University also reserves the right to cancel the market engagement event at any time and is not and shall not be liable for any costs incurred by those expressing any interest in participating in the market engagement event advertised in this notice.</P>
               <P>Interested parties will not be prejudiced by any response or failure to respond to the market engagement event and a response to this PIN does not guarantee any invitation to participate in this event or any future procurement.</P>
               <P>Note: To register your interest in this notice and obtain any additional information please visit the Sell2Wales Web Site at https://www.sell2wales.gov.wales/Search/Search_Switch.aspx?ID=77457.</P>
               <P>(WA Ref:77457).</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
            <DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2018-04-16</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>
         </COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
